n women and girls. Written for students of cultural and gender studies, parents, media literacy educators, as well as film buffs everywhere, this book aims to provide the moviegoer with the critical tools necessary to develop a resistant gaze at Hollywood productions and make healthier choices among the many viewing screens of our super-mediated world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aBody image in motion pictures. 0aHuman body in motion pictures. 0aMotion pictures -- Influence. 0aMotion pictures and women. 0aMotion picturesxInfluence. 0aWomen in motion pictures. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aPsychology : Psychology of Women. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Psychopathology / Eating Disorders.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143843530540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438435305423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438435305/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles